			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I play a wizard on Vallon Zek and I can tell you that wizards in PvP are somewhat of a toss-up.<BR>
<BR>
Wizards are capable of dealing awesome damage, with the exception of certain levels (especially lvl 39.  magic based nukes tend to suck in pvp).  It seems to me that from about level 12 to level 44, a wizard's pvp ability is restricted as a wizard's combat life is terrible, since the DD's don't do enough damage in PvP for how much mana they take.  <BR>
<BR>
One requirement, or at least one good idea for a wizard to effectively make a kill is that they must kill fast and from a distance.  If an opponent has a chance to react, it can be difficult to keep them at a sufficient distance to kill them, especially when many people stock up on MR gear.  When I was playing at lower levels, I wanted a wide open unhilled area to fight in so that I could cast shadowstep or yonder to escape battle if necessary.  At level 35 (I think it was) I killed the pegasus in SK and looted the pegasus cloak.  Since then I have found that having an unlimited supply of levitation is very handy, as most people do not have the level of mobility it grants.  Fighting melee classes is almost a joke since I can run off the sides of hills and cast on them from midair, etc.  <BR>
<BR>
Undoubtedly, though, the two hardest classes (in my opinion) to fight are Necromancers and Mages, because of their pets.  Necros are easier because they don't have many quick-killing spells, but DoT's are a fairly serious threat.  Mages I try to avoid unless their pet isn't up.  Stuns are almost worthless since they are easy to resist, so the one of the only ways to interrupt spells is with Shock of Lightning.<BR>
<BR>
There's several sides to the argument as I've played as and against wizards;  its a class that in my opinion requires a great deal of skill to PK with, especially before the 50's.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
